<br>
There are many opions about how to create an Enchanter, and how to play them. Whats important <br>
is that you ARE The ENCHANTER, as an Erudite you will start in Odus, and play your first lvl's in <br>
Toxx forest, What fun to make friends and hunt with them, looting and selling finally being able to buy your spells.<br>
<br>
Twinking: is gotta be up to you, it would be nice to buy all your spells, armor, weapon right from the beginning<br>
but lvl 1- 10 are time well spent learning your trade. I cant say I despise An Twinked enchanter, but ive seen and played with them, and i must say, that most have no finesse, what a horid sight to see an Enchanter<br>
running around acting like a tank, not to say we donot take an active role, but we do it thru Mind Control.<br>
<br>
Spells: why not buy them all, actually there is a large range of spells to chose from, USE them, take time and <br>
experiment with them, dont be afraid to make mistakes, you will develop your solo and group tactics this way.<br>
<br>
Where to hunt: after you have finished in Toxx Forest and become a bit more adventurous, take the boat to <br>
Qeynos, get a bind at the gate, and run around getting to know the city and finding the Hall of Sorcery.<br>
from Qeynos you can hunt in the Hills starting around lvl 5 or 6, hanging round the cross roads area, eventuall<br>
heading deeper in to the hills and on to blackburrow. as almost everyone knows turning in gnoll fangs to Captn Tillan will get you excellent exp and a moonstone, turning in the moonstone to Mcjacob will also get you<br>
exp and a bottle of bb stout to sell or share with your parnters. Basing out from Qeynos will allow you to<br>
hunt in Everfrost going for spidersilk, hey make your own raw silk armor, there are plenty of casters around<br>
for the demand.<br>
<br>
If you like you can run to NK and get a Tp, or wait till you get invis and make the run to where ever you wish,<br>
personally I based out of Qeynos till lvl 15 then headed to Oasis, to my surprise no one wanted to group with an Enchanter till 16 when you get Breeze, thier loss. I soloed camiens and crocks till 16 spell set, group at orc Hway till 17 them off to High pass hold orc group, then eventually moving in to the guard room in HP keep.<br>
<br>
As an Enchanter Ive had my share of up and downs (see my ongoing post, out on a limb) but all in all Ive had a great time, found an excellent Guild, and made a slew of friends. these expierences have made me a better<br>
RPGer, and a better person. EQ is not always bout lvling, getting the best gear, I made some great friends<br>
by sending out shouts forming a group for a swimming party, or shouting for fishing and drinking parties.<br>
